Address: 300 S Ashley St, Ann Arbor, MI 48104
Description: Simple 24-hour eatery serving breakfast, burgers, gyros & traditional American diner bites.

parking: Somewhat difficult to find a space

summary.snippet: "Interesting place to eat , food was good ..just ordered burger 🍔 and fries"
"Solid diner fare with breakfast options, sandwiches and fried foods."
"Food was overpriced for the quality of service received."

most_relevant.description: Fleetwood is a pretty cool 24 hour diner. A bit of a dive but in a good way. The food is pretty much your classic diner food and it’s nice that you can get breakfast, lunch, or dinner food any time. After a late night in Ann Arbor, it’s a solid place to go to for a late night meal. I feel like it’s a place that in reality is fine, but, it’ll always seem incredible because whenever you go, it’s probably super late after a night out and it just hits differently lol

Weird, cool little diner located in Ann Arbor, MI! This place has a reputation for giving very generous portions! Fleetwood Diner is best known for its Hippie Hashbrowns but almost anything on the menu is good! A very popular place, getting in to actually dine can be tricky, so I recommend getting your order to go. Parking is also challenging, but don't get discouraged, something will open up, even if you end up walking it's worth it! Staff is friendly and helpful. Food is hot, fresh and well prepared!
Nice title joint. Waitress and cook were very friendly and fast. I had the club with chili cheese fries. Simple enough. Sandwich was good but the chili tasted like cheap canned chili.

My friend and I used to love this place. We would drive 45 minutes just to order their "Hippie Hash."
So disappointed.
While eating, the cook LOUDLY complained to a coworker about personal issues. This went on for a good 15 minutes before my friend had to ask him to stop with his vulgarity. There's more, but why bother. Sadly, we won't be back.
Good luck in the bathroom. No soap, and it stinks of sewer.
*Side note, my friend wrote her review and added pictures of the diner. However, they took them down. Odd.
Reposting them.
If you can't see them, they again deleted them.

The absolute, hands-down best hippie hash I’ve ever had. The gyro meat in this meal made me instantly remember why I fell in love with gyros oh so many years ago. Was it a late night meal? Yes. Would I be at this food at any time of any day. Yes.

I've been to this diner twice, once for brunch and the other after going out at night. It has all you want for dinner vibes, good graffiti, stickers, greasy food, barstools, etc. When I went for brunch it was great I really enjoyed my meal and the outdoor patio seating was nice under the roof part. Going at night is an entirely different experience haha. I'd say the place is great for a diner but the service is a little slow. I think part of that is because it's always full and there wait staff and cooks are stretched a bit thin. This is just a fair warning that if the place is busy, the meal won't be as quick.

We had an excellent dinner here (gotta love breakfast for dinner!)

Tables inside and outside- indoors only about 6 tables, and about 4-5 counter seats.

Dog friendly on the patio.
